im periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.'),(285,'CapitalLeasesFutureMinimumPaymentsExecutoryCosts',1,2,1,'Capital Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Executory Costs','Amounts to be paid by lessee to lessor for maintenance, insurance, and tax expenses related to the leased asset.'),(286,'CapitalLeasesFutureMinimumPaymentsInterestIncludedInPayments',1,2,1,'Capital Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Interest Included in Payments','Amount necessary to reduce net minimum lease payments to present value for capital leases.'),(287,'CapitalLeasesFutureMinimumPaymentsPresentValueOfNetMinimumPayments',1,1,1,'Capital Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Present Value of Net Minimum Payments','Present value of minimum lease payments for capital leases net of executory costs, including amounts paid by the lessee to the lessor for insurance, maintenance and taxes.'),(288,'CapitalLeasesFutureMinimumSubleaseRentals',1,2,1,'Capital Leases, Future Minimum Sublease Rentals','Minimum payments receivable in the future under noncancelable subleases.'),(289,'CapitalLeasesIncomeStatementAmortizationExpense',1,2,2,'Capital Leases, Income Statement, Amortization Expense','The charge for the use of long-lived depreciable capital leased assets for the period.'),(290,'CapitalLeasesIncomeStatementDirectFinancingLeaseRevenue',1,1,2,'Capital Leases, Income Statement, Direct Financing Lease Revenue','Revenue realized in the period on direct financing leases.'),(291,'CapitalLeasesIncomeStatementInterestExpense',1,2,2,'Capital Leases, Income Statement, Interest Expense','The financing charge for leasing arrangements meeting the criteria for capitalization.'),(292,'CapitalLeasesIncomeStatementLeaseRevenue',1,1,2,'Capital Leases, Income Statement, Lease Revenue','Total amount of lease revenue realized in the period on leasing arrangements.'),(293,'CapitalLeasesIncomeStatementSalesTypeLeaseRevenue',1,1,2,'Capital Leases, Income Statement, Sales Type Lease Revenue','Revenue 