c Cost','The increase (decrease) during the reporting period in carrying amount of capitalized electric costs of a regulated entity that are expected to be recoverable through rate adjustments within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.'),(1402,'PaymentsForProceedsFromDelayedTaxExemptExchange',1,1,2,'Payments for (Proceeds from) Delayed Tax Exempt Exchange','Net cash outflow or inflow from a property which is traded for the promise to provide a replacement like-kind property in the near future also known as tax deferred exempt exchange.'),(1403,'PaymentsForProceedsFromDepositsOnRealEstateAcquisitions',1,1,2,'Payments for (Proceeds from) Deposits on Real Estate Acquisitions','Net cash outflow or inflow from the amount given in advance to show intention to complete the acquisition piece of land, anything permanently fixed to it, including buildings, structures on it, and so forth.'),(1404,'IncreaseDecreaseInDividendsReceivable',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Dividends Receivable','The increase (decrease) during the reporting period in cash disbursements due from investments, representing the shareholders\' portion of profits.'),(1405,'PaymentsForProceedsFromFederalHomeLoanBankStock',1,1,2,'Payments for (Proceeds from) Federal Home Loan Bank Stock','Amount of cash outflow (inflow) from acquisition (sale) of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) stock.'),(1406,'PaymentsForProceedsFromHedgeInvestingActivities',1,1,2,'Payments for (Proceeds from) Hedge, Investing Activities','The cash outflow or inflow for a financial contract that meets the hedge criteria as either a cash flow hedge, fair value hedge, or hedge of a net investment in a foreign operation.'),(1407,'IncreaseDecreaseInAccruedSalaries',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Accrued Salaries','The increase (decrease) during the period in accrued salaries.'),(1408,'IncreaseDecreaseInDueFromEmployeeCurrent',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Due from Employee, Current','The increase (decrease) during the reporting period in the amount due within one year (or one business cycle) from employees for floats, allowances and loans (generally evidenced by promissory notes).'),(1409,'IncreaseDecreaseInDeferredLiabilities',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Deferred Liabilities','Change during the period in carrying value for all deferred liabilities due within one year or operating cycle.'),(1410,'IncreaseDecreaseInInsuranceSettlementsReceivable',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Insurance Settlements Receivable','The increase (decrease) during the reporting period in insurance settlements receivable, which are amounts due in settlement of a claim for reimbursement from an insurance company when the Company has suffered a loss covered under an insurance policy. The expectation is that such reimbursement will be received within one year of the balance sheet date.'),(1411,'IncreaseDecreaseInNotesReceivableCurrent',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Notes Receivable, Current','The increase (decrease) during the reporting period of amounts due within one year (or one business cycle) from note holders for outstanding loans.'),(1412,'IncreaseDecreaseInOtherEmployeeRelatedLiabilities',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Other Employee-Related Liabilities','Amount of increase (decrease) in employer-related costs classified as other and current.'),(1413,'IncreaseDecreaseInOtherOperatingAssets',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Other Operating Assets','Amount of increase (decrease) in operating assets classified as other.'),(1414,'IncreaseDecreaseInLeaseAcquisitionCosts',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Lease Acquisition Costs','The increase (decrease) in the balance of capitalized lease acquisition costs during the period. The cost usually covers a variety of administrative costs, such as the cost of obtaining a credit report, verifying insurance coverage, lease commission charges, checking the accuracy and completeness of the lease documentation, and entering the lease in data processing and accounting systems.'),(1415,'P