uity and debt investments during the current period.'),(1491,'InterestExpense',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Operating and Nonoperating','Amount of interest expense classified as operating and nonoperating. Includes, but is not limited to, cost of borrowing accounted for as interest expense.'),(1492,'InterestExpenseBorrowings',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Borrowings','Aggregate amount of interest expense on all borrowings.'),(1493,'InterestExpenseTimeDeposits100000OrMore',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Time Deposits, $100,000 or More','Interest expense incurred on time deposits, including certificates of deposits, of $100,000 or more in domestic offices.'),(1494,'InterestExpenseTimeDepositsLessThan100000',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Time Deposits, Less than $100,000','Interest expense incurred on time deposits, including certificates of deposits, less than $100,000 in domestic offices.'),(1495,'InterestExpenseTimeDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Time Deposits','The aggregate interest expense incurred on time deposits, including certificates of deposits, in domestic offices.'),(1496,'InterestExpenseCommercialPaper',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Commercial Paper','Amount of interest expense on commercial paper.'),(1497,'InterestExpenseCustomerDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Customer Deposits','The interest expense recognized during the period on customer deposits or security deposits held in interest bearing accounts.'),(1498,'InterestExpenseDebt',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Debt','Amount of the cost of borrowed funds accounted for as interest expense for debt.'),(1499,'InterestExpenseDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Deposits','Aggregate amount of interest expense on all deposits.'),(1500,'InterestExpenseDemandDepositAccounts',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Demand Deposit Accounts','Interest expense incurred on demand deposit accounts that represent borrowings rather than outstanding drafts.'),(1501,'InterestExpenseMoneyMarketDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Money Market Deposits','Interest expense incurred on all money market deposits.'),(1502,'InterestExpenseNegotiableOrderOfWithdrawalNOWDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Negotiable Order of Withdrawal (NOW) Deposits','Interest expense incurred on the amount of Negotiable Order of Withdrawal (NOW). Interest-bearing transaction account that combines the payable on demand feature of checks and investment feature of savings accounts. A NOW account is functionally an interest paying checking account.'),(1503,'InterestExpenseSavingsDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Savings Deposits','Interest expense incurred on all savings account deposits.'),(1504,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilities',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities','Aggregate amount of all interest expense on domestic deposit liabilities.'),(1505,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesBrokered',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Brokered','Amount of interest expense on domestic brokered deposit liabilities.'),(1506,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesCertificatesOfDeposit',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Certificates of Deposit','Amount of interest expense on domestic certificates of deposit liabilities.'),(1507,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesChecking',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Checking','Amount of interest expense on domestic checking deposit liabilities.'),(1508,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesDemand',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Demand','Amount of interest expense on domestic demand deposit liabilities.'),(1509,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesMoneyMarket',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Money Market','Amount of interest expense on domestic money market demand account deposit liabilities.'),(1510,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesNoticeOfWithdrawal',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Notice of Withdrawal','Amount of interest expense on domestic notice of withdrawal demand deposit liabilities.'),(1511,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesOtherTimeDeposit',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Other Time Deposit','Amount of interest expense on domestic time deposit liabilities other than certificates of liabilities.'),(1512,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesRetail',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Retail','Amount of interest expense on domestic retail deposit liabilities.'),(1513,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesSavings',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Savings','Amount of interest expense on domestic savings deposit liabilities.'),(1514,'InterestExpenseDomesticDepositLiabilitiesTimeDeposit',1,2,2,'Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Time Deposit','Amount of interest expense on time deposit liabilities.'),(1515,'InterestExpenseDomesticDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Domestic Deposits','The aggregate interest expense incurred on all domestic deposits.'),(1516,'InterestExpenseFederalFundsPurchasedAndSecuritiesSoldUnderAgreementsToRepurchase',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Federal Funds Purchased and Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase','The aggregate expense incurred on federal funds purchased and securities sold under agreements to repurchase. If amounts recognized as payables under repurchase agreements have been offset against amounts recognized as receivables under reverse repurchase agreements and reported as a net amount on the balance sheet, the income and expense from these agreements may be reported on a net basis.'),(1517,'InterestExpenseFederalFundsPurchased',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Federal Funds Purchased','Gross expenses on the purchase of Federal funds at a specified price with a simultaneous agreement to sell the same to the same counterparty at a fixed or determinable price at a future date.'),(1518,'InterestExpenseSecuritiesSoldUnderAgreementsToRepurchase',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase','Gross expenses on securities sold coupled with an agreement to repurchase the same from the same counterparty at a fixed or determinable price within a fixed or variable time period.'),(1519,'InterestExpenseFederalHomeLoanBankAndFederalReserveBankAdvancesLongTerm',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank Advances, Long-Term','Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on long-term borrowings associated with Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank advances.'),(1520,'InterestExpenseFederalHomeLoanBankAndFederalReserveBankAdvancesShortTerm',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank Advances, Short-Term','Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on short-term borrowings associated with Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank advances.'),(1521,'InterestExpenseForeignDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Foreign Deposits','Interest expense on all foreign deposits.'),(1522,'InterestExpenseLesseeAssetsUnderCapitalLease',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Lessee, Assets under Capital Lease','The amount, during the lease term, of each minimum [capital] lease payment allocated to interest expense so as to produce a constant periodic rate of interest on the remaining balance of the capital lease obligation.'),(1523,'InterestExpenseLongTermDebt',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Long-Term Debt','Aggregate amount of interest paid or due on all long-term debt.'),(1524,'InterestExpenseNOWAccountsMoneyMarketAccountsAndSavingsDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, NOW Accounts, Money Market Accounts, and Savings Deposits','The aggregate interest expense incurred on the following for deposits in domestic offices: (1) transaction accounts (NOW, and telephone and preauthorized transfer accounts), (2) money market deposits and (3) savings deposits.'),(1525,'InterestExpenseOnPrepetitionLiabilitiesRecognizedInStatementOfOperations',1,2,2,'Interest Expense on Prepetition Liabilities Recognized in Statement of Operations','The amount of interest expense on prepetition obligations included in the statement of operations.'),(1526,'InterestExpenseOtherDomesticDeposits',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Other Domestic Deposits','Interest expense incurred on other deposits in domestic offices.'),(1527,'InterestExpenseOtherLongTermDebt',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Other Long-Term Debt','Amount of interest expense incurred on long-term debt classified as other, including, but not limited to, interest on long-term notes and amortization of issuance costs.'),(1528,'InterestExpenseOtherShortTermBorrowings',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Other Short-Term Borrowings','Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on other short-term borrowings.'),(1529,'InterestExpenseOther',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Other','Amount of interest expense classified as other.'),(1530,'InterestExpenseShortTermBorrowings',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Short-Term Borrowings','The aggregate interest expense incurred on short-term borrowings including commercial paper and Federal funds purchased and securities sold under agreements to repurchase.'),(1531,'InterestExpenseShortTermBorrowingsExcludingFederalFundsAndSecuritiesSoldUnderAgreementsToRepurchase',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Short-Term Borrowings Excluding Federal Funds and Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase','The aggregate interest expense incurred on short-term borrowings including commercial paper, Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank advances and other short term borrowings.'),(1532,'InterestExpenseSubordinatedNotesAndDebentures',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Subordinated Notes and Debentures','Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on subordinated notes and debentures. Includes amortization of expenses incurred in the issuance of subordinated notes and debentures.'),(1533,'InterestExpenseTradingLiabilities',1,2,2,'Interest Expense, Trading Liabilities','Interest expense incurred on short positions arising from sales of securities and other assets, which the entity does not own, to other parties. Trading liabilities includes the fair value of derivative contracts held for trading that are in loss positions.'),(1534,'InterestAndDividendIncomeSecuritiesAvailableForSale',1,1,2,'Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Available-for-Sale','Amount of operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on available-for-sale securities.'),(1535,'InterestIncomeAndFeesBankersAcceptancesCertificatesOfDepositAndCommercialPaper',1,1,2,'Interest Income and Fees, Bankers Acceptances, Certificates of Deposit and Commercial Paper','Interest and fee income derived from banker\'s acceptances, certificates of deposit and commercial paper.'),(1536,'InterestIncomeExpenseAfterProvisionForLoanLoss',1,1,2,'Interest Income (Expense), after Provision for Loan Loss','Amount of interest income or expense, including any amortization and accretion (as applicable) of discounts and premiums, including consideration of the provisions for loan, lease, credit, and other related losses.'),(1537,'InterestIncomeFederalFundsSoldAndSecuritiesPurchasedUnderAgreementsToResell',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Federal Funds Sold and Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell','The aggregate interest income earned from (1) the lending of excess federal funds to another commercial bank requiring such for its legal reserve requirements and (2) securities purchased under agreements to resell.'),(1538,'InterestIncomeFederalFundsSold',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Federal Funds Sold','Interest income on federal funds sold. Federal funds sold represent the excess federal funds held by one commercial bank which it lends to another commercial bank, usually at an agreed-upon (federal funds) rate of interest. Such loans generally are of short-duration (overnight).'),(1539,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesPurchasedUnderAgreementsToResell',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell','Interest income derived from securities purchased under agreements to resell. The difference in the price at which the institution buys the securities and resells the securities represents interest for the use of the funds by the other party. Most repurchase and sale agreements involve obligations of the federal government or its agencies, but other financial instruments, such as commercial paper, banker\'s acceptances and negotiable certificates of deposits are sometimes used in such transactions.'),(1540,'InterestAndDividendIncomeSecuritiesHeldToMaturity',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Debt Securities, Held-to-Maturity','Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on held-to-maturity securities.'),(1541,'InterestIncomeDomesticDeposits',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Domestic Deposits','Interest earned on deposits in United States money market accounts and other United States interest earning accounts.'),(1542,'InterestIncomeDepositsWithFinancialInstitutions',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Deposits with Financial Institutions','Interest income derived from funds deposited with both domestic and foreign financial institutions including funds in money market and other accounts.'),(1543,'InterestIncomeForeignDeposits',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Foreign Deposits','Interest income generated from amounts on deposit with foreign entities located outside the United States of America.'),(1544,'InterestIncomeMoneyMarketDeposits',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Money Market Deposits','Interest earned on funds deposited in US domestic money market accounts.'),(1545,'InterestIncomeOtherDomesticDeposits',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Other Domestic Deposits','Amount of interest earned on US domestic deposits classified as other. Excludes money market accounts.'),(1546,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesTaxAdvantaged',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, Operating, Tax Advantaged','Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities subject to tax benefits. Excludes operating interest income on securities exempt from state, federal and other income tax.'),(1547,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesTaxExempt',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, Operating, Tax Exempt','Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities exempt from state, federal and other income tax.'),(1548,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesTaxable',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, Operating, Taxable','Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities subject to state, federal and other income tax.'),(1549,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansCommercialIndustrialAndAgriculturalLoans',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial, Industrial, and Agricultural Loans','Interest and fee income generated from all commercial, industrial, and agricultural loans.'),(1550,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansCommercial',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial','Interest and fee income related to commercial loans including industrial and agricultural, real estate (commercial and residential, construction and development), trade financing, and lease financing.'),(1551,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansCommercialRealEstate',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial, Real Estate','Interest and fee income generated from loans secured by commercial properties. Examples of properties commonly securing commercial real estate loans may include office buildings, apartment buildings, shopping centers, industrial property, and hotels.'),(1552,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansCommercialAndResidentialRealEstate',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial and Residential, Real Estate','Interest and fee income from commercial and residential real estate loans.'),(1553,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansConsumerInstallmentAutomobilesMarineAndOtherVehicles',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer Installment, Automobiles, Marine, and Other Vehicles','Interest and fee income generated by automobile, marine, and other vehicle loans made to individuals.'),(1554,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansConsumerInstallmentCreditCard',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer Installment, Credit Card','Interest and fee income from credit card balances due from individuals. Such loans are considered revolving credit arrangements.'),(1555,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansConsumer',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer','Interest and fee income generated from consumer loans. Consumer loans are loans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures. Such loans include residential mortgages, home equity lines-of-credit, automobiles and marine transport loans, credit card transactions, and others.'),(1556,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansForeign',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Foreign','Interest and fee income generated by commercial and consumer loans, made by foreign branches of the reporting entity, which may include loans to foreign governments, foreign banks and other financial institutions, commercial and industrial entities, and citizens of not domiciled in the same country as the reporting entity.'),(1557,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansConsumerHomeEquity',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer, Home Equity','Interest and fee income from home equity lines-of-credit extended to individuals (borrowers). Such loans are generally secured by the borrower\'s equity in her or his home.'),(1558,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansLeaseFinancing',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Lease Financing','Interest and fee income generated by direct lease financing which consists of an institution owning and leasing personal property for the use of its customers at the customers\' specific request.'),(1559,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansAndLeasesHeldInPortfolio',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loan and Lease, Held-in-Portfolio','Interest and fee income generated by loans the Entity intends and has the ability to hold for the foreseeable future, or until maturity or payoff, including commercial and consumer loans, whether domestic or foreign, which may consist of: (1) industrial and agricultural; (2) real estate; and (3) real estate construction loans; (4) trade financing; (5) lease financing; (6) home equity lines-of-credit; (7) automobile and other vehicle loans; and (8) credit card and other revolving-type loans. Also includes interest income for leases held by the Entity.'),(1560,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansOtherConsumer',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Other Consumer','Interest and fee income from other loans extended to individual consumers.'),(1561,'InterestAndFeeIncomeOtherLoans',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Other Loans','Amount of interest and fee income from loans classified as other.'),(1562,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansRealEstateConstruction',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Real Estate Construction','Interest and fee income from loans used for real estate development and construction costs. Such loans are referred to as \"Construction\" loans or mortgages.'),(1563,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansConsumerRealEstate',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer, Real Estate','Interest and fee income generated from loans secured by one- to four-family residential properties. This item excludes home equity lines-of-credit.'),(1564,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansTradeFinancing',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Trade Financing','Interest and fee income generated by trade financing. Trade financing is a specialized area of commercial lending frequently used by businesses that engage in international activities. Such financing includes open account financing, sales on consignment, documentary collections, advances against collections, letters of credit, bankers\' acceptances, factoring, and forfeiting.'),(1565,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansAndLeasesHeldForSale',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loan and Lease, Held-for-Sale','The amount of interest and fee income earned from loans held-for-sale, including mortgage loans, and interest earned from direct financing and sales-type leases held-for-sale.'),(1566,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesMortgageBacked',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, Mortgage-Backed','Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securitized, pass-through debt securities collateralized by real estate mortgage loans.'),(1567,'InterestAndFeeIncomeLoansHeldForSaleMortgages',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loan, Mortgage, Held-for-Sale','Interest and fee income from mortgage loans considered to be held-for-sale.'),(1568,'InterestIncomeOperating',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Operating','Amount of operating interest income, including, but not limited to, amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts on securities.'),(1569,'OtherInterestAndDividendIncome',1,1,2,'Other Interest and Dividend Income','Amount, after discount, accretion and premium amortization, of interest income and dividend income classified as other.'),(1570,'InterestAndDividendIncomeSecuritiesOther',1,1,2,'Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Other','Amount of other operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities.'),(1571,'InterestAndFeeIncomeOtherLoansHeldForSale',1,1,2,'Interest and Fee Income, Loan, Other, Held-for-Sale','Amount of interest and fee income from loans held-for-sale and classified as other.'),(1572,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesOtherUSGovernment',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, Other US Government','Interest income on securities issued by US government agencies not including US Treasury Securities.'),(1573,'InterestAndDividendIncomeSecurities',1,1,2,'Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating','Amount of operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities.'),(1574,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesStateAndMunicipal',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, State and Municipal','Interest income, including any amortization and accretion (as applicable) of discounts and premiums, derived from debt securities issued by municipal governments, local taxing districts and US state government agencies.'),(1575,'InterestAndDividendIncomeSecuritiesTradingOrMeasuredAtFairValue',1,1,2,'Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Trading or Measured at Fair Value','Amount of operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on trading securities and other forms of securities that provide ownership interests.'),(1576,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesUSTreasuryAndOtherUSGovernment',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, US Treasury and Other US Government','Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on U.S. Treasury securities and other U.S. government securities.'),(1577,'InterestIncomeSecuritiesUSTreasury',1,1,2,'Interest Income, Securities, US Treasury','Interest income on US treasury securities. US treasury securities are negotiable debt obligations of the US government, secured by its full faith and credit and issued at various schedules and maturities. The income from treasury securities is exempt from state and local, but not federal, taxes. There are three types of securities issued by the US treasury (bonds, bills, and notes), which are distinguished by the amount of time from the initial sale of the bond to maturity.'),(1578,'UnrecognizedTaxBenefitsInterestOnIncomeTaxesExpense',1,2,2,'Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Interest on Income Taxes Expense','Amount of interest expense for an underpayment of income taxes.'),(1579,'UnrecognizedTaxBenefitsInterestOnIncomeTaxesAccrued',1,1,1,'Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Interest on Income Taxes Accrued','Amount of interest expense accrued for an underpayment of income taxes.'),(1580,'AccountsPayableInterestBeari