ent is expected to be financially capable of honoring the agreement.'),(1730,'LegalFees',1,2,2,'Legal Fees','The amount of expense provided in the period for legal costs incurred on or before the balance sheet date pertaining to resolved, pending or threatened litigation, including arbitration and mediation proceedings.'),(1731,'LitigationReserve',1,1,1,'Estimated Litigation Liability','Aggregate carrying amount of the estimated litigation liability for known or estimated probable loss from litigation, which may include attorneys\' fees and other litigation costs.'),(1732,'PaymentsOfLoanCosts',1,1,2,'Payments of Loan Costs','The cash outflow for loan origination associated cost which is usually collected through escrow.'),(1733,'LoanPortfolioExpense',1,2,2,'Loan Portfolio Expense','The loan servicing fees paid to third parties that relate to loan expenses for a portfolio containing the entire group of loans owned by the company.'),(1734,'LoansReceivableHeldForSaleAmount',1,2,1,'Financing Receivable, Held-for-Sale','Amount, before valuation allowance, of financing receivable classified as held-for-sale.'),(1735,'LoansReceivableHeldForSaleReconciliationToCashFlowAdditionsToHeldForSale',1,2,2,'Financing Receivable, Held-for-Sale, Not Part of Disposal Group, Reconciliation to Cash Flow, Addition to Held-for-Sale','Amount, after allowance for credit loss, of addition to financing receivable held for sale that is not part of disposal group.'),(1736,'LoansReceivableHeldForSaleReconciliationToCashFlowPeriodIncreaseDecrease',1,NULL,2,'Financing Receivable, Held-for-Sale, Not Part of Disposal Group, Reconciliation to Cash Flow, Period Increase (Decrease)','Amount, after allowance for credit loss, of increase (decrease) in financing receivable held for sale that is not part of disposal group.'),(1737,'LoansReceivableHeldForSaleReconciliationToCashFlowDeductionsFromHeldForSale',1,1,2,'Financing Receivable, Held-for-Sale, Not Part of Disposal Group, Reconciliation to Cash Flow, 