 includes, but is not limited to, transaction, adjustment, and change in value not defined as investing or financing activity.'),(1891,'NetChangeAnnuitiesAndInvestmentCertificates',1,2,2,'Net Change Annuities and Investment Certificates','The cash inflow or outflow for an insurance contract under which the policy holder make a lump sum payment or a series of payments in exchange for periodic payments to the policyholder beginning immediately or at some future date.'),(1892,'PaymentsForProceedsFromDepositOnLoan',1,1,2,'Payments for (Proceeds from) Deposit on Loan','The net cash inflow or outflow from resulting from payment, receipt or drawdown of cash deposit to guarantee a loan during the period.'),(1893,'IncreaseDecreaseInTimeDepositsOf100000OrMore',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Time Deposits of $100,000 or more','The increase (decrease) in time deposits equal to or greater than $100,000 per account.'),(1894,'IncreaseDecreaseInTimeDepositsOfLessThan100000',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Time Deposits of Less than $100,000','The increase (decrease) in time deposits less than $100,000 per account.'),(1895,'IncreaseDecreaseInOtherTimeDeposits',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Other Time Deposits','Amount of increase (decrease) in time deposits classified as other.'),(1896,'NetChangeContractHoldersFunds',1,2,2,'Net Change Contract Holders Funds','The cash inflow or outflow for a segregated fund account during the period.'),(1897,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfDebt',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Debt','The net cash inflow or outflow in aggregate debt due to repayments and proceeds from additional borrowings.'),(1898,'IncreaseDecreaseInDeposits',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Deposits','The net cash inflow or outflow for the increase (decrease) in the beginning and end of period deposits balances.'),(1899,'ProceedsFromPaymentsForDepositsAppliedToDebtRetirements',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Payments for) Deposits Applied to Debt Retirements','The net cash inflow or outflow from payments to deposit account and application of deposits to retire or pay down debt during the period.'),(1900,'ProceedsFromRepurchaseOfEquity',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repurchase of) Equity','The net cash inflow or outflow resulting from the entity\'s share transaction.'),(1901,'IncreaseDecreaseInFederalFundsPurchased',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Federal Funds Purchased','The net cash inflow or outflow from the fund borrowed from other financial institution arising from the insufficient reserve deposited at Federal Reserve Bank to meet legal requirement. This borrowing is usually contracted on an overnight basis at an agreed rate of interest.'),(1902,'IncreaseDecreaseInFederalFundsPurchasedAndSecuritiesSoldUnderAgreementsToRepurchaseNet',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Federal Funds Purchased and Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Net','The net cash inflow or outflow from the fund lent to other financial institution arising from the excess in reserve deposited at Federal Reserve Bank to meet legal requirement. This borrowing is usually contracted on an overnight basis at an agreed rate of interest. Also include cash inflow or outflow from investment sold under the agreement to reacquire such investment.'),(1903,'IncreaseDecreaseInFederalFundsSold',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Federal Funds Sold','The net cash inflow or outflow from the fund lent to other financial institution arising from the excess in reserve deposited at Federal Reserve Bank to meet legal requirement. This borrowing is usually contracted on an overnight basis at an agreed rate of interest.'),(1904,'ProceedsFromPaymentsForFederalFundsSoldAndSecuritiesPurchasedUnderAgreementsToResellNet',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Payments for) Federal Funds Sold and Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Net','The cash flow from the funds lent to and (borrowed from) other financial reporting institutions arising from excess or shortfall in reserve deposited at the Federal Reserve Bank to meet legal requirements. This lending and borrowing is usually contracted on an overnight basis at an agreed rate of interest. Also include cash outflow or inflow from investments purchased under the agreement to resell such investment.'),(1905,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfFirstMortgageBond',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) First Mortgage Bond','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) from long-term debt secured by a first mortgage deed of trust, containing a pledge of real property.'),(1906,'PaymentsForProceedsFromHedgeFinancingActivities',1,1,2,'Payments for (Proceeds from) Hedge, Financing Activities','The net cash outflow or inflow for a financial contract that meets the hedge criteria as either cash flow hedge, fair value hedge or hedge of net investment in foreign operations.'),(1907,'ProceedsFromPaymentsForInInterestBearingDepositsInBanks',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Payments for) in Interest-Bearing Deposits in Banks','The net cash inflow or outflow in Interest-bearing Deposits by banks in other financial institutions for relatively short periods of time including, for example, certificates of deposits.'),(1908,'NetChangeInterestBearingDepositsDomestic',1,2,2,'Net Change Interest-Bearing Deposits, Domestic','The increase (decrease) in interest-bearing deposits domestic.'),(1909,'NetChangeInterestBearingDepositsForeign',1,2,2,'Net Change Interest-Bearing Deposits, Foreign','The increase (decrease) in interest bearing deposits foreign.'),(1910,'IncreaseDecreaseInInterestAndDividendsReceivable',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Interest and Dividends Receivable','The increase (decrease) during the reporting period in the aggregate amount due to the entity in the form of unpaid interest and dividends.'),(1911,'NetChangeInterestAndNoninterestBearingDepositsDomestic',1,2,2,'Net Change Interest and Noninterest-Bearing Deposits, Domestic','The increase (decrease) in domestic interest and noninterest bearing deposits.'),(1912,'NetChangeInterestAndNoninterestBearingDepositsForeign',1,2,2,'Net Change Interest and Noninterest-Bearing Deposits, Foreign','The increase (decrease) in foreign interest and noninterest bearing deposits.'),(1913,'IncreaseDecreaseInOutstandingChecksOperatingActivities',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Outstanding Checks, Operating Activities','The change in cash during the period due to the net increase or decrease in outstanding checks, the liability that represents checks that have been issued but that have not cleared. The entity may classify these cash flows as financing or operating activities. Another element, Increase (Decrease) in Outstanding Checks, Financing Activities, represents cash flows from outstanding checks classified as financing activities.'),(1914,'IncreaseDecreaseInLoansHeldForSale',1,1,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Loan, Held-for-Sale','Amount of increase (decrease) in value of loan held with intention to sell or be securitized in near future.'),(1915,'PaymentsForProceedsFromLoansAndLeases',1,1,2,'Payments for (Proceeds from) Loans and Leases','The net cash outflow or inflow for the increase (decrease) in the beginning and end of period of loan and lease balances which are not originated or purchased specifically for resale. Includes cash payments and proceeds associated with (a) loans held-for-investment, (b) leases held-for-investment, and (c) both.'),(1916,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfLongTermDebtAndCapitalSecurities',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Long-Term Debt and Capital Securities','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) from long-term debt, finance lease obligation, and mandatorily redeemable capital security.'),(1917,'IncreaseDecreaseInDemandDeposits',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Demand Deposits','The net cash inflow or outflow in the total of all demand deposits, including checking and negotiable order of withdrawal (NOW) accounts, classified as cash flows from financing activities.'),(1918,'NetChangeNoninterestBearingDepositsDomestic',1,2,2,'Net Change Noninterest-Bearing Deposits, Domestic','The increase (decrease) in domestic noninterest bearing deposits.'),(1919,'NetChangeNoninterestBearingDepositsForeign',1,2,2,'Net Change Noninterest-Bearing Deposits, Foreign','The increase (decrease) in foreign noninterest bearing deposits.'),(1920,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfNotesPayable',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Notes Payable','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) from long-term debt supported by a written promise to pay an obligation.'),(1921,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfOtherDebt',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Other Debt','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) for debt classified as other.'),(1922,'IncreaseDecreaseInOtherDeposits',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Other Deposits','Amount of increase (decrease) in deposit liabilities classified as other.'),(1923,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfOtherLongTermDebt',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Other Long-Term Debt','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) from other long-term debt.'),(1924,'IncreaseDecreaseInOutstandingChecksFinancingActivities',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Outstanding Checks, Financing Activities','The change in cash during the period due to the net increase or decrease in outstanding checks, the liability that represents checks that have been issued but that have not cleared. The entity may classify these cash flows as financing or operating activities.'),(1925,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfPollutionControlBond',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Pollution Control Bond','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) from a long-term debt instrument issued by a state, certain agencies or authorities, a local government, or development corporation to finance the construction of air- or water-pollution control facilities, sewage, or solid waste disposal facilities.'),(1926,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfRelatedPartyDebt',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Related Party Debt','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) from long-term debt by a related party. Related parties, include, but are not limited to, affiliates, owners or officers and their immediate families, and pension trusts.'),(1927,'IncreaseDecreaseInSavingsDeposits',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Savings Deposits','The net cash inflow or outflow in the total of all savings account deposits, which may include passbook, statement savings accounts and money-market deposit accounts (MMDAs), classified as cash flows from financing activities.'),(1928,'ProceedsFromRepaymentsOfSecuredDebt',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Repayments of) Secured Debt','Amount of cash inflow (outflow) from long-term debt wholly or partially secured by collateral. Excludes tax exempt secured debt.'),(1929,'ProceedsFromPaymentsForSecuritiesPurchasedUnderAgreementsToResell',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Payments for) Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell','The net cash flow from purchases followed by sales of securities under terms of reverse repurchase agreements.'),(1930,'ProceedsFromPaymentsForInSecuritiesSoldUnderAgreementsToRepurchase',1,2,2,'Proceeds from (Payments for) in Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase','The cash flow from investments sold under the agreement to repurchase such investment.'),(1931,'IncreaseDecreaseInTimeDeposits',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Time Deposits','Net cash inflow (outflow) of time deposits.'),(1932,'IncreaseDecreaseInUndisbursedLoanFunds',1,2,2,'Increase (Decrease) in Undisbursed Loan Funds','The increase (decrease) during the reporting period in undistributed cash for loans that have been granted but not entirely funded.'),(1933,'ForeclosedAssets',1,2,1,'Repossessed Assets','Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of all assets obtained in full or partial satisfaction of a debt arrangement through foreclosure proceedings or defeasance; includes real and personal property; equity interests in corporations, partnerships, and joint ventures; and beneficial interests in trusts.'),(1934,'GainLossOnSaleOfMortgageLoans',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Sale of Mortgage Loans','The gains (losses) included in earnings that represent the difference between the sale price and the carrying value of loans made to finance real estate acquisitions. This element refers to the gain (loss) and not to the cash proceeds of the sale. This element is a noncash adjustment to net income when calculating net cash generated by operating activities using the indirect method.'),(1935,'GainLossOnSalesOfConsumerLoans',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Sales of Consumer Loans','The gains (losses) included in earning that represent the difference between the sale price and the carrying value of consumer loans. This element refers to the gain (loss) and not to the cash proceeds of the sale. This element is a noncash adjustment to net income when calculating net cash generated by operating activities using the indirect method.'),(1936,'GainLossOnSaleOfLoansAndLeases',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Sale of Loans and Leases','The gains (losses) included in earnings that represent the difference between the sale price and the carrying value of loans and leases that were sold during the reporting period. This element refers to the gain (loss) and not to the cash proceeds of the sales. This element is a noncash adjustment to net income when calculating net cash generated by operating activities using the indirect method.'),(1937,'NetIncomeLoss',1,1,2,'Net Income (Loss) Attributable to Parent','The portion of profit or loss for the period, net of income taxes, which is attributable to the parent.'),(1938,'NetIncomeLossAvailableToCommonStockholdersBasic',1,1,2,'Net Income (Loss) Available to Common Stockholders, Basic','Amount, after deduction of tax, noncontrolling interests, dividends on preferred stock and participating securities; of income (loss) available to common shareholders.'),(1939,'InterestIncomeExpenseNet',1,1,2,'Interest Income (Expense), Operating','Amount of interest income (expense) classified as operating.'),(1940,'NetInvestmentHedgeDerivativeAssetsAtFairValue',1,2,1,'Derivative Instruments in Hedges, Net Investment in Foreign Operations, Assets, Fair Value','Fair value of all derivative assets designated as hedges of net investment in foreign operations.'),(1941,'NetInvestmentHedgeDerivativeLiabilitiesAtFairValue',1,1,1,'Derivative Instruments in Hedges, Net Investment in Foreign Operations, Liabilities, Fair Value','Fair value of all derivative liabilities designated as hedges of net investment in foreign operations.'),(1942,'NetInvestmentHedgeDerivativesAtFairValueNet',1,2,1,'Derivative Instruments in Hedges, Net Investment in Foreign Operations, Assets, Fair Value, Net','Net fair value of all derivatives designated as hedges of net investment in foreign operations.'),(1943,'NetInvestmentIncome',1,1,2,'Net Investment Income','Amount, after investment expense, of income earned from investments in securities and real estate. Includes, but is not limited to, real estate investment, policy loans, dividends, and interest. Excludes realized gain (loss) on investments.'),(1944,'LoansAndLeasesReceivableAllowance',1,1,1,'Loans and Leases Receivable, Allowance','Amount of allowance to cover probable credit losses on loans and leases. Includes carryover of or adjustments to the allowance for loan losses in connection with business combinations. Excludes allowance for loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.'),(1945,'AllowanceForLoanAndLeaseLossesRealEstate',1,1,1,'Allowance for Loan and Lease Losses, Real Estate','The reserve to cover probable credit losses related to specifically identified fixed maturity real estate loans as well as probable credit losses inherent in the remainder of that loan portfolio.'),(1946,'LoansAndLeasesReceivableNetReportedAmount',1,2,1,'Loans and Leases Receivable, Net Amount','Amount after allowance and deduction of deferred interest and fees, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts, of loans and leases held in portfolio, including but not limited to, commercial and consumer loans. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans held for sale.'),(1947,'MortgageLoansOnRealEstateCommercialAndConsumerNet',1,2,1,'Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Commercial and Consumer, Net','The balance represents the amount of loans that are secured by real estate mortgages, offset by the reserve to cover probable credit losses on the loan portfolio.'),(1948,'PremiumsEarnedNetAccidentAndHealth',1,1,2,'Premiums Earned, Net, Accident and Health','Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of accident and health premiums earned.'),(1949,'PremiumsEarnedNetLife',1,1,2,'Premiums Earned, Net, Life','Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of life premiums earned.'),(1950,'PremiumsEarnedNetPropertyAndCasualty',1,1,2,'Premiums Earned, Net, Property and Casualty','Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of property and casualty premiums earned.'),(1951,'ProceedsFromSaleOfMortgageServicingRightsMSR',1,2,2,'Proceeds from Sale of Mortgage Servicing Rights (MSR)','The cash inflow from the sale of servicing rights, which contractually entitle the servicer to receive fees and ancillary revenues for performing billing, collection, disbursement and recordkeeping services in connection with a mortgage portfolio. Rights may be obtained via (1) acquisition or assumption of a servicing obligation that does not relate to financial assets of the servicer or its consolidated affiliates; or (2) by originating mortgage loans and then (a) transferring the loans to a Variable Interest Entity (VIE) in a transaction that meets the necessary transfer and classification requirements, or (b) transferring the loans in a transaction that meets the requirements for sale accounting.'),(1952,'ProceedsFromStockPlans',1,2,2,'Proceeds from Stock Plans','The cash inflow associated with the amount received from the stock plan during the period.'),(1953,'NetRegulatoryAssets',1,2,1,'Net Regulatory Assets','The net amount of all regulatory assets less all regulatory liabilities as of the end of the period.'),(1954,'MinimumNetWorthRequiredForCompliance',1,1,1,'Banking Regulation, Mortgage Banking, Net Worth, Minimum','Amount of minimum net worth required for mortgage banking as defined by regulatory framework.'),(1955,'PremiumsWrittenNet',1,1,2,'Premiums Written, Net','Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of premiums written.'),(1956,'NoninterestBearingDepositLiabilitiesDomestic',1,1,1,'Noninterest-Bearing Deposit Liabilities, Domestic','Amount of domestic noninterest-bearing deposits held by the entity, which may include demand deposits, checking, brokered and retail deposits.'),(1957,'NoninterestBearingDomesticDepositBrokered',1,1,1,'Noninterest-Bearing Domestic Deposit, Brokered','Amount of noninterest-bearing domestic third-party deposits placed by or through the assistance of a deposit broker, also known as brokered deposit liabilities.'),(1958,'NoninterestBearingDomesticDepositChecking',1,1,1,'Noninterest-Bearing Domestic Deposit, Checking','Amount of noninterest-bearing domestic checking deposit liabilities.'),(1959,'NoninterestBearingDomesticDepositDemand',1,1,1,'Noninterest-Bearing Domestic Deposit, Demand','Amount of money in noninterest-bearing domestic accounts that entitle the depositor to withdraw funds at any time without prior notice, also known as demand deposits.'),(1960,'NoninterestBearingDomesticDepositRetail',1,1,1,'Noninterest-Bearing Domestic Deposit, Retail','Amount of noninterest-bearing domestic retail deposit liabilities.'),(1961,'NoninterestBearingDepositLiabilitiesForeign',1,1,1,'Noninterest-Bearing Deposit Liabilities, Foreign','Amount of foreign noninterest-bearing deposits held by the entity which may include demand deposits, checking, brokered and retail deposits.'),(1962,'NondebtorReorganizationItemsLegalAndAdvisoryProfessionalFees',1,2,2,'Nondebtor Reorganization Items, Legal and Advisory Professional Fees','Amount of reorganization items related to legal and advisory professional fees related to entities not in bankruptcy.'),(1963,'BusinessDevelopment',1,2,2,'Business Development','Business development involves the development of products and services, their delivery, design and their implementation. Business development includes a number of techniques designed to grow an economic enterprise. Such techniques include, but are not limited to, assessments of marketing opportunities and target markets, intelligence gathering on customers and competitors, generating leads for possible sales, follow-up sales activity, formal proposal writing and business model design. Business development involves evaluating a business and then realizing its full potential, using such tools as marketing, sales, information management and customer service.'),(1964,'CommunicationsAndInformationTechnology',1,2,2,'Communications and Information Technology','The amount of expense in the period for communications and data processing expense.'),(1965,'CommunicationsInformationTechnologyAndOccupancy',1,2,2,'Communications, Information Technology and Occupancy','The aggregate amount of communications, data processing and occupancy expenses.'),(1966,'FederalDepositInsuranceCorporationPremiumExpense',1,2,2,'Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation Premium Expense','Amount of expense for Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) insurance.'),(1967,'LoanProcessingFee',1,2,2,'Loan Processing Fee','Expenses paid for obtaining loans which includes expenses such as application and origination fees.'),(1968,'OccupancyNet',1,2,2,'Occupancy, Net','Amount of net occupancy expense that may include items, such as depreciation of facilities and equipment, lease expenses, property taxes and property and casualty insurance expense.'),(1969,'OtherNoninterestExpense',1,2,2,'Other Noninterest Expense','Amount of noninterest expense classified as other.'),(1970,'PostageExpense',1,2,2,'Postage Expense','Amount of expense associated with postage.'),(1971,'SuppliesExpense',1,2,2,'Supplies Expense','Amount of expense associated with supplies that were used during the current accounting period.'),(1972,'SuppliesAndPostageExpense',1,2,2,'Supplies and Postage Expense','The aggregate amount of expenses directly related to the supplies and postage.'),(1973,'NoninterestIncome',1,1,2,'Noninterest Income','The total amount of noninterest income which may be derived from: (1) fees and commissions; (2) premiums earned; (3) insurance policy charges; (4) the sale or disposal of assets; and (5) other sources not otherwise specified.'),(1974,'BankOwnedLifeInsuranceIncome',1,1,2,'Bank Owned Life Insurance Income','Earnings on or other increases in the value of the cash surrender value of bank owned life insurance policies.'),(1975,'ConversionGainsAndLossesOnForeignInvestments',1,1,2,'Conversion Gains and Losses on Foreign Investments','Represents gains or losses resulting from transactions conducted in foreign currencies.'),(1976,'GainsLossesOnSalesOfAssets',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Disposition of Assets for Financial Service Operations','Amount of gain (loss) on sale or disposal of assets utilized in financial service operations.'),(1977,'GainsLossesOnSalesOfCreditCardPortfolio',1,1,2,'Gains (Losses) on Sales of Credit Card Portfolio','The gain (loss) resulting from the sale of credit card receivables (portfolios).'),(1978,'GainsLossesOnSalesOfOtherRealEstate',1,1,2,'Gains (Losses) on Sales of Other Real Estate','The net gain (loss) resulting from sales and other disposals of other real estate owned, increases (decreases) in the valuation allowance for foreclosed real estate, and write-downs of other real estate owned after acquisition or physical possession.'),(1979,'InsuranceCommissionsAndFees',1,1,2,'Insurance Commissions and Fees','Income from agency and brokerage operations (includes sales of annuities and supplemental contracts); service charges, commissions, and fees from the sale of insurance and related services; and management fees from separate accounts, deferred annuities, and universal life products.'),(1980,'InsuranceServicesRevenue',1,1,2,'Insurance Services Revenue','Revenue from insurance services, including net premiums earned, gain on sale of insurance block, agency management fees and insurance contract fees and commissions.'),(1981,'InvestmentBankingAdvisoryBrokerageAndUnderwritingFeesAndCommissions',1,1,2,'Investment Banking, Advisory, Brokerage, and Underwriting Fees and Commissions','Amount of fees and commissions from banking, advisory, brokerage, and securities underwriting activities. Activities include, but are not limited to, underwriting securities, private placements of securities, investment advisory and management services, merger and acquisition services, sale and servicing of mutual funds, and other related consulting fees.'),(1982,'GainLossOnSaleOfCapitalLeasesNet',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Sale of Capital Leases, Net','The net gain (loss) arising from the lessor\'s transactions involving the sale, transfer, or termination of financing agreements classified as capital leases.'),(1983,'GainLossOnSalesOfLoansNet',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Sales of Loans, Net','The net gain (loss) resulting from a sale of loans, including adjustments to record loans classified as held-for-sale at the lower-of-cost-or-market and fair value adjustments to loan held for investment purposes.'),(1984,'GainLossOnSaleOfLeasedAssetsNetOperatingLeases',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Sale of Leased Assets, Net, Operating Leases','The net gain (loss) arising from the lessor\'s sale of assets held- or available-for-lease under contractual arrangements classified as operating leases.'),(1985,'VentureCapitalGainsLossesNet',1,1,2,'Venture Capital Gain (Loss), Net','Amount of gain (loss) on venture capital activities. Includes venture capital revenue, fair value adjustments, interest and dividends, investment gain (loss) and fee or other income from venture capital activities.'),(1986,'Non