d undistributed earnings (deficit) available for dividend distribution. Includes, but is not limited to, retained earnings not appropriated for specific business purpose.'),(2730,'TreasuryStockReissuedAtLowerThanRepurchasePrice',1,2,2,'Treasury Stock Reissued at Lower than Repurchase Price','In cases when treasury stock is reissued at a price lower than the cost to repurchase, the excess difference between the selling price and cost to repurchase is charged against retained earnings (assuming that all APIC arising from treasury stock transactions has first been exhausted).'),(2731,'GainLossOnSaleOfInsuranceBlock',1,1,2,'Gain (Loss) on Sale of Insurance Block','Excess (deficiency) of net proceeds received over the net carrying value of a certain, bundled grouping of insurance policies.'),(2732,'InsuranceAgencyManagementFee',1,1,2,'Insurance Agency Management Fee','Fees earned during the period for providing management services.'),(2733,'InsuranceInvestmentIncome',1,1,2,'Insurance Investment Income','Investment income associated with the company\'s insurance services.'),(2734,'PremiumsEarnedNet',1,1,2,'Premiums Earned, Net','Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of premiums earned.'),(2735,'RevenueRecognitionSalesReturnsReserveForSalesReturns',1,1,2,'Revenue Recognition, Sales Returns, Reserve for Sales Returns','Amount of estimated sales returns.'),(2736,'RevenueFromRelatedParties',1,1,2,'Revenue from Related Parties','Amount of revenue, fees and commissions earned from transactions between (a) a parent company and its subsidiaries; (b) subsidiaries of a common parent; (c) an entity and trusts for the benefit of employees, for example, but not limited to, pension and profit-sharing trusts that are managed by or under the trusteeship of the entity\'s management; (d) an entity and its principal, owners, management, or members of their immediate families; and (e) affiliates.'),(2737,'AssetsHeldByInsuranceRegulators',1,2,1,'As